<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,962,1455]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">
Because of 
<bibRefCitation author="Poole" box="[332,479,998,1023]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" refString="Poole, R. W. (1989) Noctuidae. Lepidopterorum Catalogues. New Series. Fascicle 118, pt 1 - 3. E. J. Brill, Leiden, 1314 pp." type="book chapter" year="1989">
Poole (
<number box="[413,471,999,1023]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
incorrectly referred names 
<taxonomicName box="[794,949,998,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Xanthomantis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[794,949,998,1023]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Xanthomantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1110,998,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Tambana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1007,1110,998,1023]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Tambana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1428,998,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Trisuloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1304,1428,998,1023]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Trisuloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we include to this revision the data, diagnoses and illustrations of the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1044,1200,1034,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Xanthomantis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1044,1200,1034,1059]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Xanthomantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in order to show the differences between these taxa. Herewith we treat 
<taxonomicName box="[715,871,1070,1095]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Xanthomantis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[715,871,1070,1095]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Xanthomantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[908,1031,1070,1095]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pantheinae">Pantheinae</taxonomicName>
genus close to 
<taxonomicName box="[1203,1306,1070,1095]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Tambana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1203,1306,1070,1095]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Tambana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="326" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,962,1455]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1106,1131]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Wingspan 
<quantity box="[449,574,1107,1131]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" unit="mm" value="43.5" valueMax="44.0" valueMin="43.0">43–44 mm</quantity>
. Closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[793,896,1106,1131]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Tambana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[793,896,1106,1131]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Tambana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Antennae of male pectinate, labial palps short, compressed. Vein M 
<quantity box="[385,429,1142,1167]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
hindwing well developed. Forewing blackish-grey with black dentate or waved pattern; hindwing yellow or orange-yellow; abdomen black. In male genitalia, uncus straight, moderately wide; juxta shield-like; valva sclerotised, moderately wide, constricted and pointed apically; costa well developed; sacculus narrow; harpe massive, straight, relatively short. Aedeagus massive; vesica tubular-bulbous, with 
<number box="[1269,1310,1251,1275]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
patches of moderate spine-like cornuti. In female genitalia, papillae anales wide, quadrangular; anterior and posterior apophyses on a wide base, equal in length; antrum wide, shallow; ductus bursae short, sclerotised; corpus bursae large, with sclerotisation in caudal part.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,962,1455]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">The genus includes two species, both distributed almost sympatrically in the Manchurian subregion of the Palaearctic and partially in the Oriental region.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
